# nzbweaver 0.1

I wanted a nzb-downloader to use from bash. I didn't find one.

---

## âœ¨ Features

- Parses NZB files and retrieves referenced articles via NNTP (SSL/TLS supported)
- Decodes YEnc-encoded binaries using **[rapidyenc](https://github.com/animetosho/rapidyenc)**

---

## ðŸ§± Dependencies

To build nzbweaver, youâ€™ll need:

- **CMake â‰¥ 3.10**
- **C17-compatible compiler** (tested w. gcc version 15.2.1)
- **OpenSSL**
- **libexpat**
- **libpcre**
- **rapidyenc** (included as a git submodule)
- **par2verify/par2repair** (optional)
- **unrar** (optional)

On Arch Linux:
sudo pacman -S openssl expat pcre cmake make gcc

ðŸ”§ Building

git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/theknurz/nzbweaver.git
cd nzbweaver
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make -j$(nproc)

The resulting binary will be located in build/src/.

âš™ï¸ Usage

Generate and edit a configuration:
nzbweaver -s > ~/.nzbweaver.cfg

Download a NZB:
nzbweaver <file.nzb> [opt. options]

nzbweaver will:

    Parse the NZB file
    Connect to the configured NNTP server
    Retrieve and decode the referenced articles
    Optionally validate/unpack using available PAR2/RAR files

